# Vercel Infrastructure Configuration
# 
# This file demonstrates the structure of the encrypted .env file.
# The actual values are encrypted using dotenvx and stored in .env
#
# To set up locally:
# 1. Create a .env.keys file with your DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY
# 2. Run: npx dotenvx run -- your-command
#
# For CI/CD (GitHub Actions):
# 1. Set DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY secret in GitHub Actions settings
# 2. The workflow will automatically decrypt before running Terraform

# Your Vercel organization/team ID
# Get from: https://vercel.com/account/settings
VERCEL_ORG_ID=your-org-id-here

# Your Vercel API token
# Generate at: https://vercel.com/account/tokens
# Required scopes: Full Access
VERCEL_TOKEN=your-vercel-token-here
